description: Number of inequivalent strings of 2n digits, when 2 strings are equivalent if turning 1 upside down gives the other.
references: N. G. de Bruijn, Polya's theory of counting, in Beckenbach, ed., Applied Combinatorial Math., Wiley, 1964 (p. 182).
J.-P. Delahaye, 'Le miraculeux "lemme de Burnside"','La bande de chiffres' pp 146 in 'Pour la Science' (French edition of 'Scientific American') No.350 December 2006 Paris.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
